title: For Trade:  Shiloh Sharps Percussian Carbine
postcontent: Early Farmingdale Shiloh Sharps Percussian carbine. 54 cal black powder. These carbines used a paper cartridge. Plenty of information online on how to make them. Shiloh manufacturing has an excellent reputation for making high quality Sharps firearms. They were located in Farmingdale, New York before moving to Montana. Don't confuse these with some cheap imports ! This carbine was probably built in the 1980s and does show some wear, but overall is still very nice. Mostly cosmetic wear consistent with age. The two major defects are someone put tacks in the stock and the clean out screw is seized. The tack holes are an easy fix, an iron, a little glue, and light sanding will take care of them. I already started working on it.The seized clean out screw is a common issue. Most people just clean through the nipple. A good machinest can drill it out and replace it with a hex head in no time.
